docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:50:- 002E now explicitly depends on 002D2: staff login/current-user wiring should call the backend directly from Vite origin `http://localhost:5173` without a frontend proxy, use `/auth/me/` after login and after reload, and save CORS evidence for health/auth calls.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:51:- 002EX now explicitly depends on 002E and 002D2: its tracer screen must run through authenticated staff session state, use real APIs and persistent dev SQLite for manual smoke evidence, keep automated tests on the migrated Django test database, and include an unauthenticated `401` envelope regression for at least one tracer endpoint.
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:52:- 002E completed the frontend bridge: staff auth defaults to backend login → `/auth/me/`, demo staff role switching is gated by `VITE_ENABLE_DEMO_AUTH === "true"`, current-user display uses `/auth/me/` `roles`/`teams`, compatibility `role_codes`/`team_codes` are derived from those objects, and existing route/sidebar checks use an explicit canonical-backend-permission to prototype-permission mapping. Unmapped canonical permissions intentionally grant no UI access (A-010).
docs/working/digests/epic-002-platform-auth.md:54:  - 002E maps unknown backend roles to prototype `auditor` in `mapBackendUserToFrontendUser()`. Because `Dashboard`, `MyProfile`, and other shell pages still branch on `currentUser.role`, backend roles such as `it_head` or `management_viewer` can inherit auditor-shaped dashboard/profile content even with empty permissions. Corrective slice `002E2` must replace this with a neutral/no-affordance path and test zero-permission/unmapped roles.
