- 002G completed admin user-management shell: backend routes under `/api/v1/admin/users/` list/detail users with the `/auth/me/` `roles[{role_code, role_name}]` and `teams[{team_code, team_name}]` shape, bind only existing active `Role`/`Team` rows, set status to `active`/`suspended`, audit role/team/status changes, and revoke active sessions when a user is suspended. Backend gate requires a session-bound active access token plus at least one canonical user-admin permission (`users.user.create`, `users.user.update`, `users.user.disable`); frontend maps those to prototype `manage_users` and adds `admin-users` to `allNavItems`, `PAGE_PERMISSIONS`, and the app route guard. A-014 records the source-silent last active `system_admin` guard: role/status changes that would leave zero active `system_admin` users return `400 VALIDATION_ERROR`.
- For 002H: keep the workflow guard foundation domain-neutral. A shared backend transition guard may define from-state, to-state, required permission, action code, and audit/workflow-event metadata, but must not encode loan eligibility, sanction authority, money amounts, or document-completeness rules. Migrate only the existing tracer transition proof to the shared guard and preserve its public endpoint behavior and `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION` / `403 PERMISSION_DENIED` envelopes.
- For 002I: build only a domain-neutral object-level permission helper/test harness. It should accept explicit actor permissions/team codes plus object owner/team facts, allow owner or matching team access, deny missing module permission as `PERMISSION_DENIED`, deny mismatched or unknown object scope as object access denied, and avoid adding public endpoints or querying future loan/member/application tables.
- 002H completed the shared workflow guard foundation. `sfpcl_credit/workflows/guard.py` defines domain-neutral transition definitions/results plus typed errors for unknown action, missing permission, and invalid state. Tracer services now pass explicit actor permission codes into the shared guard for lifecycle actions while preserving existing tracer URLs, success payloads, `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`, `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`, audit logs, and workflow events. No schema change.
- Architecture review 2026-07-04_135247 found one corrective follow-up before 002I: 002G's backend admin gate treats any one of `users.user.create`, `users.user.update`, or `users.user.disable` as full user-management authority. Source extract: `auth-permissions.md` §12.1 defines `users.user.read`, `users.user.create`, `users.user.update`, and `users.user.disable` as distinct risk-rated permissions; §15.12 grants System Administrator create/update/disable plus role/config permissions; §19 maps `/settings/users` to `users.user.read`. Corrective slice `002G2` must add action-specific backend permission tests and preserve existing system-admin access.
- 002G2 completed the action-aware admin permission gate. `admin_views._authenticated_admin` now takes per-action required permission code sets from `admin_users`: list/detail read needs `users.user.read` OR any write user-admin permission (read fallback per A-015 because seeded `system_admin` lacks `users.user.read`); role assignment and team add/remove need `users.user.update`; suspend needs `users.user.disable`; restore-to-active needs `users.user.update`. `set_status` authorises after parsing the target status (`status_permission_codes`) so suspend and restore are gated differently; check order is `401`→`403`→`400`/`404`, and forbidden partial-permission writes create no `AuditLog` and revoke no session. The now-unused `has_manage_users_permission` helper was removed (`MANAGE_USERS_PERMISSION_CODES` is retained as the read fallback + frontend `manage_users` mapping set). Regression tests cover create-only, update-only, disable-only, and read-only partial roles plus the negative audit/session side effects. No schema change; frontend nav/route unchanged.
- For 002J: create a test-only API contract assertion harness. Use existing endpoints as fixtures: `/auth/me/` for success envelope, admin users for pagination and `403`, tracer invalid state for `409`, and an internal sample for `available_actions` shape. Do not add public endpoints or production dependencies.

## For 002EX — Early End-to-End Tracer Bullet
- Endpoints implemented under `/api/v1/tracer/`: create member, create application, sanction, create account, disburse, post repayment, close.
- Minimal statuses only: member `active`; application `draft -> sanctioned`; account `pending_disbursement -> active -> closed`; repayment `posted`.
- Guardrails tested: positive amounts only; invalid state transitions return `409 INVALID_STATE_TRANSITION`; missing bearer auth returns `401 AUTH_REQUIRED`; revoked access sessions return `401 INVALID_TOKEN`; authenticated users without `tracer.lifecycle.run` return `403 PERMISSION_DENIED`; zero-permission/unmapped frontend roles do not map tracer permissions.
