docs/source/auth-permissions.md:2625:Django built-in permissions can be used for broad CRUD, but SOP-specific permissions should be explicit custom permission codes.
docs/source/auth-permissions.md:2629:- Store permissions in DB.
docs/source/auth-permissions.md:2630:- Seed permissions through migrations / fixtures.
docs/source/auth-permissions.md:2631:- Use custom service: `permission_service.has_permission(user, permission_code)`.
docs/source/auth-permissions.md:2632:- Use decorators or DRF permission classes.
docs/source/auth-permissions.md:2633:- Use object access service for object-level checks.
